The paper deals with distributed query processing over peer-to-peer networks, which is a topic that falls under the categories of distributed computing (cs.DC), databases (cs.DB), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also considers network capabilities and transmission rates, which are relevant to the sub-category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper proposes an adaptive approach to query processing, which could be considered a form of machine learning or artificial intelligence, and thus could also fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
